parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift into neutral, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the service shifter warning light is illuminated
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or misfire, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle has a loud ticking or tapping noise
the vehicle has a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift into neutral, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the clutch pedal sticks to the floor

or blurred vision. In some cases
the plastic clips inside the headrest break
causing the headrest to push forward and alter the sitting position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and engine problems can cause engine failure, fires, and accidents.
